The key difference is safer lifetime management: `std::thread` must be manually joined or detached, while `std::jthread` auto-joins on destruction and integrates cooperative cancellation via `std::stop_token`.
Example:
std::jthread worker([](std::stop_token st){
  while (!st.stop_requested()) {
    // loop until asked to stop
  }
});
// leaving scope requests stop and joins

